The paper discusses clustering with deep learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a systematic taxonomy for clustering with deep learning and evaluates the performance of new methods. The paper also uses image datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses natural language processing, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
